    "plan_content": "Here's the complete implementation plan for the PulseBoard channel plugin:\n\n---\n\n## Plan Summary\n\n**7 new files** under `extensions/pulseboard/` — no existing files modified.\n\n### Key Architectural Decisions\n\n1. **`getChatChannelMeta` limitation**: The function only accepts pre-registered `ChatChannelId` values (e.g., `\"telegram\"`, `\"nostr\"`, `\"irc\"`). Calling it with `\"pulseboard\"` would be a TypeScript error. The plan imports it per the requirement, but defines `meta` as a direct `ChannelMeta` object literal — the same pattern used by the Nostr plugin.\n\n2. **`PluginRuntime` type**: Imported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` (no local `api.ts` barrel needed for a minimal stub).\n\n3. **Outbound adapter**: Uses the simple flat form `{ deliveryMode, textChunkLimit, sendText }` matching Nostr, with `attachChannelToResult` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-send-result` to build the result.\n\n4. **`ChannelId` casts**: `\"pulseboard\"` is not in the `ChannelId` branded union; intentional `as ChannelId` casts are used instead of `any`.\n\n5. **All stubs are minimal**: Config returns `[]`/empty stub, setup returns `cfg` unchanged, gateway logs and returns, messaging trims whitespace, sendText returns a stub result.\n\n### File Overview\n\n| File | Pattern Reference |\n|---|---|\n| `package.json` | `extensions/nostr/package.json` |\n| `openclaw.plugin.json` | `extensions/nostr/openclaw.plugin.json` |\n| `src/types.ts` | 3 clean interfaces |\n| `src/runtime.ts` | `extensions/nostr/src/runtime.ts` |\n| `src/channel.ts` | `extensions/nostr/src/channel.ts` (flat outbound) |\n| `index.ts` | `extensions/nostr/index.ts` |\n| `setup-entry.ts` | `extensions/nostr/setup-entry.ts` |\n\n### Verification\n- `pnpm tsgo` / `pnpm check` to confirm the new files type-check and lint cleanly\n- `pnpm test -- src/plugins` for manifest invariant checks\n- `pnpm openclaw channels status` to confirm the plugin is recognized",
